The paper deals with the links between enaction and artificial intelligence, specifically in terms of co-evolution with humans in the loop. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories, as these are the most relevant fields for discussing the integration of human interaction into artificial systems. The paper also discusses the use of interactive guidance systems and minimal enactive interfaces, which are relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper explores the phenomenology of interactions, which is relevant to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
